      <title>[Letter] 1833 Apr. 14, Nashville [to] Sarah B. Hamilton, Russellville, K[entuck]y / Mortimer Hamilton</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter dated April 14, 1833 to Sarah B. Hamilton from her son Mortimer Hamilton. Hamilton informs his mother of a murder in Nashville, a friends desire to purchase a young girl, and writes in length about his desire to become a Christian.</abstract>
